== 5...Bg4 · Steiner variation ==
Instead of the usual [[../5...Bf5|5...Bf5]], Black opts to put the bishop on g4, harassing White's knight. However, because the e-pawn hasn't advanced, the knight isn't actually pinned to the queen, so White can play '''6. Ne5''' with a tempo on the Bishop.

After the bishop retreats with 6...Bh5, White has the option to go for either 7. f3, preparing e4, or 7. g3, preparing to fianchetto.

